<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- A major, 3/4 waltz feel, 30 measures + pickup. Tonal center clearly on A major.
- I (A): A2-E3-A3-C#4 "334" — full, resonant pedal harp sound with C1 pedal option
- V (E): E2-B2-E3-G#3 "334" — dominant always with G#3 for brightness
- V7 (E7): adds D4 as 7th when space permits
- vi (F#m): F#2-C#3-F#3-A3 — smooth vi, leads back to I by step
- IV (D): D2-A2-D3-F#3 — open IV, lighter
- ii (Bm): B2-F#3-B3 "334" — ii for pre-dominant function
- iii (C#m): C#3-G#3-C#4 — appears once (m12) as color chord

Quartal color not used — A major benefits from rich triadic support.
7th chords (V7) used at cadential points for resolution energy.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bass line: A2→E2→A2→E2 (oscillation) creates waltz rocking motion.
- Inner voice E3 is common tone between I (A-E-A-C#) and V (E-B-E-G#) — held.
- vi (F#m) arises naturally: F#2-C#3 bass in vi shares C# with I.
- m11: D#4 melody note (chromatic passing) — harp stays on V/vi harmony (diatonic).
- m25-27: Climax at high E5/D5/C#5 — RH rises to E5/C#5, LH sustains full chords.
- m28: IV→ii→I — 3-chord descending cadential motion, bass D2→B2→A2.

TEXTURE ARC:
- m1-8: Sparse opening (2+3 notes), block chords, establish A major center.
- m9-16: Building, quarter-note chord changes in some bars (m5, m21), texture fills.
- m17-24: Development, V7 tensions, reaching upward to E5 in m24.
- m25-30: Climax m25-27 (E5/D5 melody, 3-note RH + 4-note LH), then graceful
  cadential descent: IV→ii→I in m28, V→I in m29-30, final dotted-half on A.
-->
